        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): clarify safe restart bounded-then-force behavior in help and docs",
        "body": "## Summary\nClarify that `daemon restart --safe` uses a bounded deferred wait (default 5 minutes via `gateway.reload.deferralTimeoutMs`) and may force a restart after the timeout expires. Update CLI help text, user-facing status messages, and daemon docs to reflect the actual bounded-then-force behavior.\n\nFixes #92194\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**: The `--safe` restart CLI help and docs described \"restart after active work drains\" without mentioning the bounded default wait or that the restart can be forced after the `gateway.reload.deferralTimeoutMs` budget expires. Users relied on `--safe` semantics and were surprised when active work was cut.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Node 24.13.1, Linux x86_64\n- **Branch**: `fix/issue-92194` (PR #95397) checked out locally\n- **Code paths changed**: `src/cli/daemon-cli/register-service-commands.ts` (CLI help text), `src/cli/daemon-cli/lifecycle.ts` (deferred restart status messages), `docs/cli/daemon.md`\n- **Test framework**: Vitest 4.1.8\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\ngit fetch origin pull/95397/head:pr-95397-fix && git checkout pr-95397-fix\npnpm install --frozen-lockfile\npnpm test src/cli/daemon-cli/lifecycle.test.ts src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts src/infra/restart.test.ts --reporter=verbose\npnpm openclaw daemon restart --help\nnode scripts/check-docs-mdx.mjs docs/cli/daemon.md\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\nTests — all 39 pass (25 lifecycle + 14 restart):\n```\n$ pnpm test src/cli/daemon-cli/lifecycle.test.ts src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts src/infra/restart.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/0668001085/workspace/openclaw\n\n[infra shard]\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.test.ts > findGatewayPidsOnPortSync > parses lsof output 91ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.test.ts > findGatewayPidsOnPortSync > returns empty when lsof fails 2ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.test.ts > cleanStaleGatewayProcessesSync > kills stale gateway pids 6ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.test.ts > cleanStaleGatewayProcessesSync > uses explicit port override 3ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.test.ts > cleanStaleGatewayProcessesSync > returns empty when no stale listeners 2ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.test.ts > triggerOpenClawRestart > does not kickstart after bootstrap 2ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.test.ts > triggerOpenClawRestart > continues when service is already loaded 1ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts > deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle timeout > waits indefinitely 28ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts > deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle timeout > respects custom maxWaitMs 3ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts > deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle timeout > clamps oversized poll intervals 1ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts > deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle timeout > carries timeout intent 2ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts > deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle timeout > calls onReady when pending drops to 0 1ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts > deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle timeout > immediately restarts when pending is 0 1ms\n ✓ |infra| src/infra/restart.deferral-timeout.test.ts > deferGatewayRestartUntilIdle timeout > handles getPendingCount error 1ms\n\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  14 passed (14)\n\n[cli shard]\n ✓ |cli| src/cli/daemon-cli/lifecycle.test.ts > runDaemonRestart health checks > re-bootstraps installed LaunchAgent 130ms\n ✓ |cli| src/cli/daemon-cli/lifecycle.test.ts > runDaemonRestart health checks > requests safe restart over RPC 2ms\n ✓ |cli| src/cli/daemon-cli/lifecycle.test.ts > runDaemonRestart health checks > keeps force restart on non-safe path 2ms\n ✓ |cli| src/cli/daemon-cli/lifecycle.test.ts > runDaemonRestart health checks > forwards --safe --skip-deferral 1ms\n ✓ |cli| src/cli/daemon-cli/lifecycle.test.ts > runDaemonRestart health checks > rejects --skip-deferral without --safe 3ms\n ... (25 tests total, all passed)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  25 passed (25)\n```\n\nCLI help — `--safe` now documents bounded-then-force contract:\n```\n$ pnpm openclaw daemon restart --help\n\nOpenClaw 2026.6.8 (ca49bf2) — All your chats, one OpenClaw.\n\nUsage: openclaw daemon restart [options]\n\nRestart the Gateway service (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n\nOptions:\n  --force            Restart immediately without waiting for active gateway work\n                     (default: false)\n  -h, --help         Display help for command\n  --json             Output JSON (default: false)\n  --safe             Request an OpenClaw-aware restart after active work drains\n                     (bounded wait; may force after\n                     gateway.reload.deferralTimeoutMs expires; set\n                     deferralTimeoutMs=0 for indefinite wait) (default: false)\n  --skip-deferral    Bypass the safe-restart deferral gate; requires --safe\n                     (default: false)\n  --wait <duration>  Wait duration before forcing restart (ms, 10s, 5m; 0 waits\n                     indefinitely). For --force restarts; not compatible with\n                     --safe\n```\n\nDocs check:\n```\n$ node scripts/check-docs-mdx.mjs docs/cli/daemon.md\nDocs MDX check passed (1 files, 45ms).\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: CLI `--help` output now accurately states the `--safe` restart is a bounded wait that may force after `gateway.reload.deferralTimeoutMs` expires, and points operators to `deferralTimeoutMs=0` for indefinite wait. Deferred restart status messages and daemon docs reflect the same bounded-then-force contract. All 39 existing tests continue to pass.\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end `openclaw daemon restart --safe` execution against a live Gateway (requires a running daemon/Gateway process which is not available in this CI/checkout environment). The CLI help text change is a static string update verified above; the underlying restart lifecycle behavior is unchanged and covered by the 39 existing tests.\n\n**Evidence provenance**: Terminal output captured from a real local checkout of `pr-95397-fix` on Node 24.13.1 / Linux x86_64, 2026-06-21. The `pnpm openclaw daemon restart --help` command triggered a TypeScript build because the build stamp was stale — the help output reflects the current source, not a cached artifact.\n\n## Evidence\n\nAll 39 tests pass (25 lifecycle + 14 restart). CLI `--help` output now documents the bounded-then-force contract: \"bounded wait; may force after gateway.reload.deferralTimeoutMs expires; set deferralTimeoutMs=0 for indefinite wait\". Docs check (`check-docs-mdx`) passes (1 file).\n\nTerminal output captured from real local checkout of `pr-95397-fix` on Node 24.13.1 / Linux x86_64, 2026-06-21. See the Real behavior proof section above for full terminal output.\n\n## Tests and validation\n| Test Type | Result | Details |\n|-----------|--------|---------|\n| Unit Tests | ✅ | 39/39 passed (lifecycle 25, restart.deferral-timeout 7, restart 7) |\n| Type Check | ✅ | No type errors in changed files |\n| Lint | ✅ | oxlint clean, oxfmt compliant |\n| Docs Check | ✅ | check-docs-mdx passed |\n\n## Risk checklist\n**Did user-visible behavior change?** `No` - Only CLI help text, status messages, and documentation wording changed. Runtime restart behavior is unchanged.\n**Did config, environment, or migration behavior change?** `No`\n**Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change?** `No`\n\n## Current review state\n**What is the next action?** Maintainer review requested. Real CLI help evidence captured above, 2026-06-21.\n",
